The former Vice-Chancellor of the University of Benin (UNIBEN), Professor Osayuki Godwin Oshodin, is dead. According to a statement signed by his brother, Mr. Christopher Oshodin, the Emeritus professor died in the early hours of Sunday May 29, 2022 in Benin City, Edo State after a brief illness. Oshodin died at the age 71 years. -Advertisement- The statement read, “It is a time of grief for us children, and family as we mourn his sudden death. “The family shall in no distant time release details of his burial arrangement just as we pray to God to comfort those he left behind in this period of our mourning.”